com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.provider

Class MarketPriceItems

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.provider.MarketPriceItems

  • public class MarketPriceItems
extends java.lang.Object
    This handles storage of all market price items.

    Provides methods generation of market price data, for managing the list, and a method for encoding a market price message and payload.

        public int encodeResponse(com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.Channel channel,
                          ItemInfo itemInfo,
                          com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.TransportBuffer msgBuf,

                          com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.DataDictionary dictionary,
                          com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.Error error)
        Encodes the market price response. Returns success if encoding succeeds or failure if encoding fails.
        Parameters:
        channel - - The channel to send a market price response to
        itemInfo - - The item information
        isSolicited - - The response is solicited if set
        msgBuf - - The message buffer to encode the market price response into
        streamId - - The stream id of the market price response
        isStreaming - - Flag for streaming or snapshot
        isPrivateStream - - Flag for private stream
        serviceId - - The service id of the market price response
        dictionary - - The dictionary used for encoding
        error - - error in case of encoding failure
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
